summary: GPT-NER is a framework that adapts large language models (LLMs) for named entity recognition (NER) by transforming sequence labeling tasks into text generation tasks, marked with special tokens. It addresses LLM hallucination issues through self-verification and achieves comparable performance to supervised baselines, excelling in low-resource and few-shot scenarios where labeled data is scarce.
